<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-18T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-18T10:00:00-05:00" n="328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1100 Rogers, James H./38:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-18T11:00:00-04:00">May 18, 1934—11
                                a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>136. Reference your May 17, 5 p.m. Please inform Rogers urgently that
                            discussion with Chinese officials of possible loan involves traversing
                            delicate political ground. Department believes he should under no
                            circumstances receive or discuss any proposal for loan unless and until
                            expressly instructed to do so. Department expects to discuss portions of
                            his telegram with Treasury today.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>